article.headline: S. Dakota St. 76, Idaho 58
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho (AP) -- Kai Williams scored 24 points as he led the South Dakota State Jackrabbits to a 76-58 win over the Idaho Vandals on Wednesday night. Garrett Callahan added 16 points for South Dakota State (3-2) while Ben Beran and Clint Sargent added 15 points and 10 points, respectively. Jordan Brooks paced Idaho (1-4) with 24 points. Clyde Johnson added 12 for the Vandals, which defeated SDSU twice last season for two of their four wins. The Jackrabbits led 34-33 at halftime. The two teams battled back and forth for the first part of the second half, before South Dakota State closed out the game on a 26-9 run. Williams led the charge, scoring 15 of his points after the break. Idaho's Brooks, who scored 15 points in the first half, collected his fourth foul with 14:14 left to play and sat for nearly five minutes. South Dakota State shot 54.9 percent (28-for-51) for the game, while Idaho managed to convert just 38.2 percent (21-for-55) of its field goal attempts.
